In a speech delivered at South Carolina State University, President Joe Biden praised the university and its graduates while discussing a range of topics, including his personal experiences, the importance of historically black colleges and universities (HBCUs), and his administration's plans for education, infrastructure, criminal justice reform, and voting rights. He emphasized the need for graduates to lead in addressing challenges such as hate and racism and to seize the opportunities presented by advancements in science and technology. President Biden also highlighted the role of HBCUs in producing successful professionals and pledged his support for these institutions. He concluded by urging the graduates to meet the moment and contribute to shaping the future of the country.